Package: cwsd
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: CW sender daemon for ham-radio transceivers
 cwsd runs next to your transceiver and exposes it on the network through
 several independent, individually toggled services: a Hamlib rigctld interface
 (query/set frequency, mode, PTT, VFO), a cwdaemon interface that keys text as
 Morse, an optional Opus-over-UDP receiver-audio stream, and an optional
 timestamped-edge service for real paddle keying over the internet.
 .
 It ships a systemd service that runs cwsd as a dedicated, unprivileged system
 user (added to the dialout and audio groups) reading its configuration from
 /etc/cwsd/cwsdrc.
